HEADWORD: Kerasin
<hw>Ker"a*sin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A nitrogenous substance free from phosphorus, supposed
to be present in the brain; a body closely related to
cerebrin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kerasine</ent>⟦br⟧
